                    </div>
                    <div class="blog_para">
                        <p>The world is now probably familiar with the term "optical fiber". These fiber optic cables
                            connect you to the internet, data transmission, and telephone. However, the concept of fiber
                            optics as a technical solution is much broader. It is an innovative form of data
                            transmission that allows information to be transferred efficiently at an incredible speed.
                    </div>
                    <div class="blog_list">
                        <h3>What is Optical Fiber?</h3>
                        <p>Fiber optics are cables that primarily consist of fiber and elements that shield and protect
                            the transmission lines. They are conductors that allow data to be transmitted using light
                            waves. By adapting the transmission to the speed of light, information can be transmitted at
                            ultra-high speed. Therefore, this is an innovative solution. <br>
                            Today, all areas of science related to data transmission are built on the concept of optical
                            fiber. Fiber optic technology constantly evolves to increase transmission capacity and
                            transmit more data.<br>
                            In the long run, the total cost of ownership, including installation, maintenance and use,
                            is lower than other options. Fiber optics are a long-term solution that requires little
                            maintenance. In addition, maintenance costs decrease over time.

                    </div>
                    <div class="benifits">
                        <h3>Ways in which Optical Fiber has transformed the World of Data Transmission: - </h3>


                        <h4>Deliver Data </h4>
                        <p>Fiber optics have a huge impact on homes around the world. While data rates over copper
                            cables increase by tens of megabits yearly, fiber optics brings gigabits to the home. This
                            is driving the on-demand video streaming revolution, and Gigabit fiber broadband is driving
                            the digital services revolution. <br>
                            Despite the harsh environment, fiber optics offer higher reliability than twisted pair
                            copper cable or coaxial copper wire in homes and offices, reducing cable costs and
                            environmental impact. Also, fiber optics are less likely to be dug up and sold as scrap.

                        </p>

                        <h4>Medical Benefits </h4>
                        <p>Fiber isn't just about data. Fiber optic technology is constantly opening up new medical
                            procedures. The technology is helping in finding more ways to detect and address all kinds
                            of illnesses and medical challenges. For instance, A fiber with a small camera helps the
                            surgeon see almost any part of the body for the examination. This is an important part of
                            keyhole surgery that annually helps millions of people worldwide. <br>
                            It can also transmit high-power laser light to accurately cut outgrowth and tumors,
                            minimizing damage to surrounding tissue not possible with conventional scalpels and knives.

                        </p>

                        <h4>Carry the internet </h4>
                        <p>
                            Fiber optics offer high data rates. Japanese NTT researchers show a data transmission rate
                            of 768 Tbps over a 30 fiber core cable, but the 2021 record could be surpassed in 2022, as
                            the world demands more and more data. Fibre optic cables are laid in oceans. <br>
                            They are connected by repeaters that act as amplifiers and use element-doped fibers such as
                            erbium to amplify data signals as they travel worldwide. Fibers and repeaters, laid in the
                            depths of the ocean and in the harshest environments on earth, connecting all the Internet
                            nodes and deliver petabytes of data daily.


                        </p>
                        <h4>Enable the quantum revolution </h4>
                        <p>The foundation of optical fiber dates back to 1960s but this technology is at the forefront
                            of the latest developments in quantum cryptography.<br>
                            With the introduction of quantum computers to the market, it has become possible to decipher
                            today's cryptographic algorithms, and new technologies are in great need. This comes from
                            quantum cryptography, which uses two entangled photons. <br>
                            No matter where you are in the world, one photon cannot be intercepted or modified without
                            affecting the other and can be used as an encryption key. Fiber optic cables distribute keys
                            from the sender to the receiver. This Quantum Key Distribution (QKD) allows you to securely
                            send the financial, government, and personal data worldwide from eavesdropping.

                        </p>

                        <h4>Feel the world </h4>
                        <p>The fiber optic sensors additionally called as optical fiber sensors use optical fiber or
                            sensing element.
                            These sensors are utilized to detect a few amounts like temperature, pressure, vibrations,
                            relocations.<br>
                            Fiber optics can be installed in concrete to monitor building stresses and strains that
                            cannot be detected otherwise.<br>
                            It can also measure well temperatures and provide data from the harshest environments
                            without being affected by electromagnetic interference. <br>
                            The fibers woven into the fabric provide temperature data while generating electricity for
                            portable computers. Fiber optics also enables modern flight experience by allowing
                            kilometers of dope fiber wrapped around a gyroscope can detect motion with far higher
                            accuracy than GPS navigation and ships worldwide.


                        </p>


